occurrenceRemarks: This is a young adult female alterna. Amazingly, she was encountered as she was crossing the highway at 3:45 pm in full bright sunlight. The temp was 79 degrees F. She was laid out straight as an arrow, with her nose at the edge of the road. I was traveling at about 75 mph when I saw her. I thought she was a dead snake and I turned around to take a pic for INat. She left the road and was in grass at the base of a low rock cut.
